Preheat oven to 425 degrees. Bring a large #pot{} of salted water and @cracked freekeh{3/4%cup} to a boil. Reduce to a simmer, cook until tender, ~{20-25%minutes}. Drain and rinse under cold water.

Wash and dry all produce. Meanwhile, trim and halve @Brussels sprouts{8%ounce}. Thinly slice half the Brussels sprouts into shreds.

Roast the veggies: Toss remaining Brussels sprouts and @butternut squash{8%ounce} on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @olive oil{1%teaspoon} and a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}. Roast ~{10-13%minutes}, toss, then continue roasting until golden brown, another ~{10-13%minutes}.

Heat a drizzle of olive oil in a pan over medium heat. Add shredded Brussels sprouts, and toss until softened, ~{3-4%minutes}. Season with salt and pepper.

Halve, peel, and mince @shallot{1%unit}. Zest and halve @lemon{1%unit}. Whisk together shallots, lemon zest, juice of half a lemon, and @olive oil{2%tablespoon} in a large #bowl{}. Season with salt and pepper. Taste and adjust with more olive oil, if necessary.

Toss and serve: Core and dice @Fuji apple{1%unit}. Toss freekeh, shredded Brussels sprouts, @Parmesan cheese{1/2%cup}, and diced apples into citronette dressing. Season with salt and pepper. Plate freekeh salad, and top with roasted Brussels sprouts and butternut squash. Enjoy!